tafsir[11]{c,v,t}:
  83,36,"(Are not the disbelievers paid) rewarded in the Hereafter (for what they used to do) except for what they used to do and say in the life of the world?'"
  84,1,"And from his narration on the authority of Ibn 'Abbas that he said regarding the interpretation of Allah's saying (When the heaven is split asunder): '(When the heaven is split asunder) by the clouds because of the descent of the Lord-a descent without any modality-and the angels and whatever Allah wills of His command."
  84,3,"(And when the earth is spread out) like the spreading out of a flat plain; and it is also said this means: when the earth is removed from its place and then flattened."
  84,5,"(And attentive) and obeys and listens (to her Lord in fear!) and it behoves her do so."
  84,7,"(Then whoso is given his account) the account of his good works (in his right hand) in reference here to Abu Salamah Ibn 'Abd al-Asad"
  84,8,"(He truly will receive an easy reckoning) this refers to his parade before Allah"
  84,9,"(And will return) in the Hereafter (unto his folk) whom Allah prepared for him in Paradise (in joy) with them."
  84,11,"(He surely will invoke destruction"
  84,12,"And be thrown to scorching fire."
  84,14,"(He verily deemed that he would never return (unto Allah)) in the Hereafter."
  84,23,"(And Allah knoweth best what they are hiding) and Allah knows best what they say and do; and it is also said this means: Allah knows best what they hear and hide in their hearts."